    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Install a debug Focus Nightly build 107.0a1, that has the widget prompt implemented.\r\n2. Open a page.\r\n3. Tap on the trashcan.\r\n4. When the widget prompt is displayed, tap on the \"Add widget to home screen\" button.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe second prompt is displayed that asks the user to add the widget to the home screen.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe widget prompt is dismissed without other actions from the user. The widget is not added.\r\nThe widget can be added by the user without issues, via the long-tap on the home screen - select \"Widgets\" - select and drag manually the Focus Nightly widget.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Sony Xperia Z5 Premium (Android 7.1.1), Samsung Galaxy Tab A6 (Android 5.1.1), **Xiaomi mi8 Lite (Android 10)**\r\n* Focus version: Focus Nightly 107.0a1 debug build\r\n* In [7506](https://github.com/mozilla-mobile/focus-android/issues/7506#issue-1340257236), was mentioned that \"Android 5, 6 and 7 users **don\u2019t see this message** (the population is too small)\", but the widget prompt is displayed!\r\n* The logcat: [logcat.txt](https://github.com/mozilla-mobile/focus-android/files/9625584/logcat.txt)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/191742546-5131f3ec-d8d9-40b8-a0fc-d6feb7eb515a.mp4\r\n\r\n",
